        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-09T23:47:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the \"(int, \" notation is confusing -- I assume the int here is the unique identifier?  Seems like \"immutable set\" ought to introduce the \"{ ... }\" part.  As with timelines, I wouldn\u0027t consider the fence\u0027s identifier part of the state of the fence, but rather a naming scheme for accessing fences.  If you explain this identifier, move the statement of \"aka fence fd\" next to that.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 85,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "cfba63e2a3244bbebcbb650faa8174c0b62a09e9",
