        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-09T23:47:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"timeline-id-value\" is a new, undefined term.  I think you want to say what you said for timeline: \"...of (timeline-id, value) pairs.\"  Then maybe \"Each pair indicates a timeline, and the value that the timeline\u0027s value must reach for the fence to become signaled\".  (Or satisfied, if you like that terminology.)\n\nDid you mean to be introducing timeline-id-value as the name for the \u003ctimeline-id, value\u003e pair, perhaps?  You use it that way below, with timeline-id-values sounding like a set of such pairs.  If so, you need to introduce the definition of that here.  Something like:\n\n   \"Let timeline-id-value be a pair of (timeline-id, value), and let timeline-id-values be a set of such pairs.  A fence is a timeline-id-values set.\"",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 86,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 86,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "cfba63e2a3244bbebcbb650faa8174c0b62a09e9",
